         = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n\n'''Pulayanarkotta''' is a locality in [[Thiruvananthapuram]], [[Kerala]], [[India]].\n\n==Meaning of the name==\nPulayanarkotta literally means the fort of the [[Pulayar|Pulaya's]] [[King]].\n\n==History==\nThe ''Pulayanarkotta'' [[region]] was ruled by a [[dynasty]] belonging to the [[Pulayar|Pulaya community]] is said to be and Pulayanarkotta is also famous with a story about the Kalipulayan who the last [[Pulayar|Pulaya]] king of Pulayanarkotta and his clan which is not  added in the Kerala history.a temple dedicated to him has been left at [[Attakulangara]] in [[Thiruvananthapuram]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/the-forgotten-king-of-pulayanarkotta/article6383352.ece|title=The forgotten king of Pulayanarkotta|first=Achuthsankar S.|last=Nair|date=September 5, 2014|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mathrubhumi.com/thiruvananthapuram/nagaram/-malayalam-news-1.1323009|title=\u0d15\u0d25\u0d15\u0d33\u0d4a\u0d34\u0d3f\u0d2f\u0d3e\u0d24\u0d46 \u0d2a\u0d41\u0d32\u0d2f\u0d28\u0d3e\u0d7c\u0d15\u0d4b\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f|first=\u0d1c\u0d3f|last=\u0d2e\u0d39\u0d47\u0d37\u0d4d\u200c|website=Mathrubhumi}}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Native Life in Travancore|year=1883|chapter=There is a deep mention of Pulayanarkotta in Samuel Mateer's book |url=https://books.google.com.bh/books/about/Native_Life_in_Travancore.html?id=aYdCAAAAIAAJ&redir_esc=y |isbn=978-8120605145 |authorlink=Samuel Mateer}}</ref>\n\n==Organisations based in Pulayanarkotta==\nThe Government Indian Institute of Diabetes center<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/chest-diseases-hospital-to-be-upgraded/article25561329.ece|title=Chest Diseases Hospital to be upgraded|first=Staff|last=Reporter|date=November 22, 2018|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dhs.kerala.gov.in/index.php/thiurvananthapuram.html|title=Thiurvananthapuram}}</ref> \n\nThe Government T.B Centre and Chest Diseases Hospital  .<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/thiruvananthapuram/2016/may/24/TB-centre-at-pulayanarkotta-cries-for-attention-907176.html|title=TB centre at pulayanarkotta cries for attention|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/trips-to-pulayanarkotta-choke-patients-381716.html|title=Trips to Pulayanarkotta choke patients|date=July 5, 2011|website=News18}}</ref>\n\n[[Southern Air Command (India)]].\n\n==Religious institutions==\n*Kunjuveedu Kovil\n*Kunnam Siva Temple\n*Idiyadikkodu Bhagavathi Temple\n*Peadikkadu Pangiyamma Bhagavathi Temple Trust\n*Sree Bhagavathikkavu Devi Temple\n*Juma Masjid\n*Moosa Moulana Guidance Centre Masjid\n*Kumarapuram Juma Masjid\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ulloor]]\n*[[Kazhakoottam]]\n*[[Attakulangara]]\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Thiruvananthapuram district}}\n\n[[Category:Suburbs of Thiruvananthapuram]]\n[[Category:Thiruvananthapuram]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Suburb in Thiruvananthapuram}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Pulayanarkotta\n| native_name_lang        =ml\n| other_name              =\u0d2a\u0d41\u0d32\u0d2f\u0d28\u0d3e\u0d7c\u0d15\u0d4b\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = village\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India Kerala\n| pushpin_label_position  = left\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = \n| coordinates             = {{coord|8.5203731|N|76.9122711|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Kerala]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Thiruvananthapuram]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| esta